      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Blockages are rarely random; they typically stem from specific foreign object debris (FOD) common to the flight environment, such as metallic shrapnel, rocks, or ice crystals, rather than random elements. Insects are indeed a frequent cause because their bodies can lodge in the narrow forward opening, but the primary safety concern is usually metallic fragments or ice that can totally seal the orifice. Airlines and maintenance crews use visual inspections and strobe lights to detect these specific hazards before flight.",
