    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It seems like even a tiny bit of debris can cause a huge issue for the sensors. Since it's such a small, critical opening, is there any way to protect the tube from those kinds of obstructions during ground operations, or are pilots just supposed to keep a close eye on it?",
